In cases where a Dataset contains more than one abstract (for example, one might be supplied by the data producer and another prepared by the data repository where the data are deposited), the date attribute is used to distinguish between the two abstracts The date attribute follows the ISO convention of YYYY-MM-DD.

Key terms that describe important aspects of the Dataset. Are used for classification and retrieval purposes. The vocabulary attribute is provided for specification of the controlled vocabulary in use, ELSST (European Language Social Science Thesaurus). The vocabURI attribute specifies the location for the full controlled vocabulary.
The vocabulary attribute is provided for specification of the controlled vocabulary in use. In this case, ELSST (European Language Social Science Thesaurus).

Keyword vocabulary URL points to the web presence that describes the keyword vocabulary, if appropriate. Enter an absolute URL where the keyword vocabulary web site is found, such as https://elsst.ukdataservice.ac.uk/.
The classification field indicates the broad important topic (s) and subjects that the data cover. CESSDA topic classification may be used here.
